section.p:
The quickest way to get started is to obtain one of the pre-built packages. Even when adding additional functionalities to Hippo ECM, you normally don't need to rebuild Hippo ECM. This because more functionality can be added by simply adding the JARs containing the add-ons to the already packaged product, or uploading them into the running packaged product. Therefore, there is no need to do a rebuild from all the sources, one of the two pre-built packages can always be customized.
The quickstart packages contain all the core packaged products, but have been pre-configured with a number of modules and settings, to give you a quick overview of the product, without having the laborious tasks to first enter content, create users, etcetera.
Hippo ECM is a web-based application, and therefor is intended to run inside a servlet or application container. These containers accept pre-built applications in the form of a WAR or EAR archive package, and provide basic functions to Hippo ECM and management of your application. To get you started quickly, first determine the platform you wish to use to run Hippo ECM. Then;
